    {
        "content": "<p>Then, the question is, how on earth did you get an element in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>H</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">H^{1+p}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">+</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>?!<br>\n(For example, for the composition of <code>Ext</code>-groups, I did not define a map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mi>a</mi></msup><mo>×</mo><mi>E</mi><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mi>b</mi></msup><mo>→</mo><mi>E</mi><mi>x</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Ext^a \\times Ext^b \\to Ext^{a+b}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t