    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/W37PaJvEfUzm_ftGDI_yl9WM/Screenshot-2026-01-31-at-19.14.21.png\">Screenshot 2026-01-31 at 19.14.21.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/W37PaJvEfUzm_ftGDI_yl9WM/Screenshot-2026-01-31-at-19.14.21.png\" title=\"Screenshot 2026-01-31 at 19.14.21.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"1611x1407\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/W37PaJvEfUzm_ftGDI_yl9WM/Screenshot-2026-01-31-at-19.14.21.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><p>the context here is I'm trying to state the two commutative diagrams ((ii) is where the main issue is) about cup product and chasing the upper half of the diagram gives me <code>p + q + 1</code> where chasing the other half gives me <code>p + 1 + q</code></p>",
